Анализ A/B-теста¶

График кумулятивной выручки по группам¶

In [15]:
cum_revenue = orders.groupby(['date', 'group']).agg({'revenue': 'sum'}).groupby('group').cumsum().reset_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for group in cum_revenue['group'].unique():
    plt.plot(cum_revenue[cum_revenue['group'] == group]['date'],
             cum_revenue[cum_revenue['group'] == group]['revenue'],
             label=f'Group {group}')
plt.title('   ')
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('(.)')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

cum_orders = orders.groupby(['date', 'group']).agg({'transactionId': 'count'}).groupby('group').cumsum().reset_index()

cum_data = cum_revenue.merge(cum_orders, on=['date', 'group'])

cum_data['average_order_value'] = cum_data['revenue'] / cum_data['transactionId']

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for group in cum_data['group'].unique():
    plt.plot(cum_data[cum_data['group'] == group]['date'],
             cum_data[cum_data['group'] == group]['average_order_value'],
             label=f'Group {group}')
plt.title('    ')
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('  (.)')

Статистическая значимость различий в среднем количестве заказов на посетителя между группами по «сырым» данным¶

H_0: .

$H_0: \mu_{\ \ } = \mu_{\ \ }$

H_1: .

$H_1: \mu_{\ \ } \neq \mu_{\ \ }$

In [25]:
ordersByUsersA = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'A']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique})
)
ordersByUsersA.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders']

ordersByUsersB = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'B']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique})
)
ordersByUsersB.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders']

visitorsA_ids = orders[orders['group'] == 'A']['visitorId'].unique()
visitorsB_ids = orders[orders['group'] == 'B']['visitorId'].unique()

ordersByUsersA = pd.concat([ordersByUsersA['orders'],pd.Series(0, index=np.arange(visitors[visitors['group']=='A']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersA['orders'])), name='orders')],axis=0)
ordersByUsersB = pd.concat([ordersByUsersB['orders'],pd.Series(0, index=np.arange(visitors[visitors['group']=='B']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersB['orders'])), name='orders')],axis=0)

ordersByUsersA = pd.DataFrame(ordersByUsersA)
ordersByUsersA.columns = ['orders']
ordersByUsersB = pd.DataFrame(ordersByUsersB)
ordersByUsersB.columns = ['orders']

p_value_raw_orders = stats.mannwhitneyu(ordersByUsersA['orders'], ordersByUsersB['orders'])[1]
mean_diff_raw_orders = ordersByUsersB['orders'].mean() / ordersByUsersA['orders'].mean() - 1

p_value_raw_orders, mean_diff_raw_orders
print("p-value: {0:.3f}".format(p_value_raw_orders))
print(" : {0:.3f}".format(mean_diff_raw_orders))

ordersByUsersA = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'A']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique})
)
ordersByUsersA.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders']

ordersByUsersB = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'B']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique})
)
ordersByUsersB.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders']

ordersByUsers = pd.concat([ordersByUsersA, ordersByUsersB])


sampleA = pd.concat([ordersByUsersA['orders'],pd.Series(0, index=np.arange(visitors[visitors['group']=='A']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersA['orders'])), name='orders')],axis=0)
sampleB = pd.concat([ordersByUsersA['orders'],pd.Series(0, index=np.arange(visitors[visitors['group']=='A']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersA['orders'])), name='orders')],axis=0)

usersWithManyOrders = pd.concat(
    [
        ordersByUsersA[ordersByUsersA['orders'] > 2]['visitorId'],
        ordersByUsersB[ordersByUsersB['orders'] > 2]['visitorId'],
    ],
    axis=0,
)
usersWithExpensiveOrders = orders[orders['revenue'] > 28000]['visitorId']
abnormalUsers = (
    pd.concat([usersWithManyOrders, usersWithExpensiveOrders], axis=0)
    .drop_duplicates()
    .sort_values()
)
sampleAFiltered = pd.concat(
    [
        ordersByUsersA[
            np.logical_not(ordersByUsersA['visitorId'].isin(abnormalUsers))
        ]['orders'],
        pd.Series(
            0,
            index=np.arange(
                visitors[visitors['group']=='A']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersA['orders'])
            ),
            name='orders',
        ),
    ],
    axis=0,
)

sampleBFiltered = pd.concat(
    [
        ordersByUsersB[
            np.logical_not(ordersByUsersB['visitorId'].isin(abnormalUsers))
        ]['orders'],
        pd.Series(
            0,
            index=np.arange(
                visitors[visitors['group']=='B']['visitors'].sum() - len(ordersByUsersB['orders'])
            ),
            name='orders',
        ),
    ],
    axis=0,
)

sampleAFiltered = pd.DataFrame(sampleAFiltered)
sampleAFiltered.columns = ['orders']
sampleBFiltered = pd.DataFrame(sampleBFiltered)
sampleBFiltered.columns = ['orders']


p_value_clean_orders = stats.mannwhitneyu(sampleAFiltered['orders'], sampleBFiltered['orders'])[1]
mean_diff_clean_orders = sampleBFiltered['orders'].mean() / sampleAFiltered['orders'].mean() - 1

print("p-value: {0:.3f}".format(p_value_clean_orders))
print(" : {0:.3f}".format(mean_diff_clean_orders))

ordersByUsersA = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'A']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique, 'revenue': 'sum'})
)
ordersByUsersA.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders', 'revenue']

ordersByUsersB = (
    orders[orders['group'] == 'B']
    .groupby('visitorId', as_index=False)
    .agg({'transactionId': pd.Series.nunique, 'revenue': 'sum'})
)
ordersByUsersB.columns = ['visitorId', 'orders', 'revenue']

ordersByUsers = pd.concat([ordersByUsersA, ordersByUsersB])

abnormalUsers = ordersByUsers[(ordersByUsers['orders'] > 2) & (ordersByUsers['revenue'] > 28000)]['visitorId']

filtered_orders_A = orders[np.logical_and(orders['group'] == 'A', np.logical_not(orders['visitorId'].isin(abnormalUsers)))]
filtered_orders_B = orders[np.logical_and(orders['group'] == 'B', np.logical_not(orders['visitorId'].isin(abnormalUsers)))]

p_value_clean_revenue = stats.mannwhitneyu(filtered_orders_A['revenue'], filtered_orders_B['revenue'])[1]
mean_diff_clean_revenue = filtered_orders_B['revenue'].mean() / filtered_orders_A['revenue'].mean() - 1

print("p-value: {0:.3f}".format(p_value_clean_revenue))
print(" : {0:.3f}".format(mean_diff_clean_revenue))

p-value: 0.926
 : 0.304

  • - 0.304 , B 30.4% , A.
